Statements must not have a value pushed onto the stack,
however, in the cast of expression statements, the value IS pushed onto the
stack, we solve this by keeping track of the loop, and making sure to pop
all values off the stack before jumping to the top. There should be a better
way to do this at compile time. To figure out if an expression statement should
have it's value popped